{"snp5.19":{"snp5.19:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.19 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.19 ","html":"<article id='snp5.19'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.19:0.2":{"pli":"Pārāyanānugītigāthā ","eng":"Preserving the Way to the Far Shore ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.19:1.1":{"pli":"“Pārāyanamanugāyissaṃ, ","eng":"“I shall keep reciting the Way to the Far Shore,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"To <i lang='pi' translate='no'>anugāyati</i> is to keep on reciting, as the brahmins did with their hymns descended from seers of old (as eg. <a href='index.html?q=an5.192#3.1'>AN 5.192:3.1</a>). "},"snp5.19:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā piṅgiyo) ","eng":"said Venerable Piṅgiya, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:1.3":{"pli":"Yathāddakkhi tathākkhāsi; ","eng":"“which was taught as it was seen ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:1.4":{"pli":"Vimalo bhūrimedhaso, ","eng":"by the immaculate one of vast intelligence. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:1.5":{"pli":"Nikkāmo nibbano nāgo; ","eng":"He is desireless, unentangled, a spiritual giant: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:1.6":{"pli":"Kissa hetu musā bhaṇe. ","eng":"why would he speak falsely? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:2.1":{"pli":"Pahīnamalamohassa, ","eng":"Come, let me extol ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:2.2":{"pli":"mānamakkhappahāyino; ","eng":"in sweet words of praise ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:2.3":{"pli":"Handāhaṃ kittayissāmi, ","eng":"the one who’s given up stains and delusions, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:2.4":{"pli":"giraṃ vaṇṇūpasañhitaṃ. ","eng":"conceit and contempt. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:3.1":{"pli":"Tamonudo buddho samantacakkhu, ","eng":"The Buddha, all-seer, dispeller of darkness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:3.2":{"pli":"Lokantagū sabbabhavātivatto; ","eng":"has gone to world’s end, beyond all rebirths; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:3.3":{"pli":"Anāsavo sabbadukkhappahīno, ","eng":"he is free of defilements, <j>and has given up all suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:3.4":{"pli":"Saccavhayo brahme upāsito me. ","eng":"the rightly-named one, brahmin, is revered by me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:4.1":{"pli":"Dijo yathā kubbanakaṃ pahāya, ","eng":"Like a bird that flees a little copse, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:4.2":{"pli":"Bahupphalaṃ kānanamāvaseyya; ","eng":"to roost in a forest abounding in fruit, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:4.3":{"pli":"Evampahaṃ appadasse pahāya, ","eng":"I’ve left the near-sighted behind, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:4.4":{"pli":"Mahodadhiṃ haṃsoriva ajjhapatto. ","eng":"like a swan come to a great river. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:5.1":{"pli":"Ye me pubbe viyākaṃsu, ","eng":"Those who explained to me previously, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:5.2":{"pli":"Huraṃ gotamasāsanā; ","eng":"before Gotama’s teaching, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:5.3":{"pli":"Iccāsi iti bhavissati, ","eng":"said ‘thus it was’ or ‘so it shall be’. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:5.4":{"pli":"Sabbaṃ taṃ itihītihaṃ; ","eng":"All that was just the testament of hearsay; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:5.5":{"pli":"Sabbaṃ taṃ takkavaḍḍhanaṃ. ","eng":"all that just fostered speculation. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:6.1":{"pli":"Eko tamanudāsino, ","eng":"Alone, the dispeller of darkness ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:6.2":{"pli":"jutimā so pabhaṅkaro; ","eng":"is brilliant, a beacon: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:6.3":{"pli":"Gotamo bhūripaññāṇo, ","eng":"Gotama, vast in wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:6.4":{"pli":"gotamo bhūrimedhaso. ","eng":"Gotama, vast in intelligence. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:7.1":{"pli":"Yo me dhammamadesesi, ","eng":"He is the one who taught me Dhamma, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:7.2":{"pli":"Sandiṭṭhikamakālikaṃ; ","eng":"apparent in the present life, immediately effective, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:7.3":{"pli":"Taṇhakkhayamanītikaṃ, ","eng":"the untroubled, the end of craving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:7.4":{"pli":"Yassa natthi upamā kvaci”. ","eng":"to which there is no compare.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:8.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃ nu tamhā vippavasasi, ","eng":"“Why would you dwell apart from him ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"This verse and the next were apparently spoken by Bāvarī. "},"snp5.19:8.2":{"pli":"muhuttamapi piṅgiya; ","eng":"even for an hour, Piṅgiya? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:8.3":{"pli":"Gotamā bhūripaññāṇā, ","eng":"From Gotama, vast in wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:8.4":{"pli":"gotamā bhūrimedhasā. ","eng":"from Gotama, vast in intelligence? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:9.1":{"pli":"Yo te dhammamadesesi, ","eng":"He is the one who taught you Dhamma, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:9.2":{"pli":"Sandiṭṭhikamakālikaṃ; ","eng":"apparent in the present life, immediately effective, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:9.3":{"pli":"Taṇhakkhayamanītikaṃ, ","eng":"the untroubled, the end of craving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:9.4":{"pli":"Yassa natthi upamā kvaci”. ","eng":"to which there is no compare.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:10.1":{"pli":"“Nāhaṃ tamhā vippavasāmi, ","eng":"“I never dwell apart from him, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:10.2":{"pli":"Muhuttamapi brāhmaṇa; ","eng":"not even for an hour, brahmin. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:10.3":{"pli":"Gotamā bhūripaññāṇā, ","eng":"From Gotama, vast in wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:10.4":{"pli":"Gotamā bhūrimedhasā. ","eng":"from Gotama, vast in intelligence. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:11.1":{"pli":"Yo me dhammamadesesi, ","eng":"He is the one who taught me Dhamma, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:11.2":{"pli":"Sandiṭṭhikamakālikaṃ; ","eng":"apparent in the present life, immediately effective, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:11.3":{"pli":"Taṇhakkhayamanītikaṃ, ","eng":"the untroubled, the end of craving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:11.4":{"pli":"Yassa natthi upamā kvaci. ","eng":"to which there is no compare. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:12.1":{"pli":"Passāmi naṃ manasā cakkhunāva, ","eng":"Being diligent, I see him ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:12.2":{"pli":"Rattindivaṃ brāhmaṇa appamatto; ","eng":"in my mind’s eye day and night. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:12.3":{"pli":"Namassamāno vivasemi rattiṃ, ","eng":"I spend the night in homage to him, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:12.4":{"pli":"Teneva maññāmi avippavāsaṃ. ","eng":"hence I think I dwell with him. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:13.1":{"pli":"Saddhā ca pīti ca mano sati ca, ","eng":"My faith and joy and intent and mindfulness ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:13.2":{"pli":"Nāpentime gotamasāsanamhā; ","eng":"never stray from Gotama’s teaching. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:13.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ yaṃ disaṃ vajati bhūripañño, ","eng":"I bow to whatever direction ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:13.4":{"pli":"Sa tena teneva natohamasmi. ","eng":"the one of vast wisdom heads. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:14.1":{"pli":"Jiṇṇassa me dubbalathāmakassa, ","eng":"I’m old and feeble, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:14.2":{"pli":"Teneva kāyo na paleti tattha; ","eng":"so my body cannot go there, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:14.3":{"pli":"Saṅkappayantāya vajāmi niccaṃ, ","eng":"but I always travel in my thoughts, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:14.4":{"pli":"Mano hi me brāhmaṇa tena yutto. ","eng":"for my mind, brahmin, is bound to him. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:15.1":{"pli":"Paṅke sayāno pariphandamāno, ","eng":"Lying floundering in the mud, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:15.2":{"pli":"Dīpā dīpaṃ upaplaviṃ; ","eng":"I drifted from island to island. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:15.3":{"pli":"Athaddasāsiṃ sambuddhaṃ, ","eng":"Then I saw the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:15.4":{"pli":"Oghatiṇṇamanāsavaṃ”. ","eng":"the undefiled one who has crossed the flood.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:16.1":{"pli":"“Yathā ahū vakkali muttasaddho, ","eng":"“Just as Vakkali was committed to faith—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"This verse is apparently spoken by the Buddha. "},"snp5.19:16.2":{"pli":"Bhadrāvudho āḷavigotamo ca; ","eng":"Bhadrāvudha and Gotama of Āḷavī too—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:16.3":{"pli":"Evamevaṃ tvampi pamuñcassu saddhaṃ, ","eng":"so too you should commit to faith. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:16.4":{"pli":"Gamissasi tvaṃ piṅgiya maccudheyyassa pāraṃ”. ","eng":"You will go, Piṅgiya, beyond the domain of death.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:17.1":{"pli":"“Esa bhiyyo pasīdāmi, ","eng":"“My confidence grows ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:17.2":{"pli":"Sutvāna munino vaco; ","eng":"as I hear the word of the sage, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:17.3":{"pli":"Vivaṭṭacchado sambuddho, ","eng":"the Buddha with veil cast off, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:17.4":{"pli":"Akhilo paṭibhānavā. ","eng":"so kind and eloquent. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:18.1":{"pli":"Adhideve abhiññāya, ","eng":"Having directly known all about the gods, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"That <i lang='pi' translate='no'>adhideva</i> means “about the gods” is established at <a href='index.html?q=mn90#17.8'>MN 90:17.8</a>. "},"snp5.19:18.2":{"pli":"Sabbaṃ vedi varovaraṃ; ","eng":"he understands all top to bottom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:18.3":{"pli":"Pañhānantakaro satthā, ","eng":"the teacher who settles all questions ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:18.4":{"pli":"Kaṅkhīnaṃ paṭijānataṃ. ","eng":"for those who admit their doubts. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:19.1":{"pli":"Asaṃhīraṃ asaṅkuppaṃ, ","eng":"The unfaltering, the unshakable: ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:19.2":{"pli":"Yassa natthi upamā kvaci; ","eng":"that to which there is no compare. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:19.3":{"pli":"Addhā gamissāmi na mettha kaṅkhā, ","eng":"For sure I will go there, I have no doubt of that. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:19.4":{"pli":"Evaṃ maṃ dhārehi adhimuttacittan”ti. ","eng":"Remember me as one whose mind is made up.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.19:19.5":{"pli":"Pārāyanavaggo pañcamo. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p>"},"snp5.19:19.6":{"pli":"Suttuddānaṃ ","html":"<p class='uddana-intro'>{}</p>"},"snp5.19:20.1":{"pli":"Urago dhaniyopi ca, ","html":"<blockquote class='uddanagatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:20.2":{"pli":"Khaggavisāṇo kasi ca; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:20.3":{"pli":"Cundo bhavo punadeva, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:20.4":{"pli":"Vasalo ca karaṇīyañca; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:20.5":{"pli":"Hemavato atha yakkho, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:20.6":{"pli":"Vijayasuttaṃ munisuttavaranti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:21.1":{"pli":"Paṭhamakaṭṭhavaro varavaggo, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:21.2":{"pli":"Dvādasasuttadharo suvibhatto; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:21.3":{"pli":"Desito cakkhumatā vimalena, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:21.4":{"pli":"Suyyati vaggavaro uragoti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:22.1":{"pli":"Ratanāmagandho hirimaṅgalanāmo, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:22.2":{"pli":"Sucilomakapilo ca brāhmaṇadhammo; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:22.3":{"pli":"Nāvā kiṃsīlauṭṭhahano ca, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:22.4":{"pli":"Rāhulo ca punapi vaṅgīso. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:23.1":{"pli":"Sammāparibbājanīyopi cettha, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:23.2":{"pli":"Dhammikasuttavaro suvibhatto; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:23.3":{"pli":"Cuddasasuttadharo dutiyamhi, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:23.4":{"pli":"Cūḷakavaggavaroti tamāhu. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:24.1":{"pli":"Pabbajjapadhānasubhāsitanāmo, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:24.2":{"pli":"Pūraḷāso punadeva māgho ca; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:24.3":{"pli":"Sabhiyaṃ keṇiyameva sallanāmo, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:24.4":{"pli":"Vāseṭṭhavaro kālikopi ca. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:25.1":{"pli":"Nālakasuttavaro suvibhatto, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:25.2":{"pli":"Taṃ anupassī tathā punadeva; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:25.3":{"pli":"Dvādasasuttadharo tatiyamhi, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:25.4":{"pli":"Suyyati vaggavaro mahānāmo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:26.1":{"pli":"Kāmaguhaṭṭhakaduṭṭhakanāmā, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:26.2":{"pli":"Suddhavaro paramaṭṭhakanāmo; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:26.3":{"pli":"Jarā mettiyavaro suvibhatto, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:26.4":{"pli":"Pasūramāgaṇḍiyā purābhedo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:27.1":{"pli":"Kalahavivādo ubho viyuhā ca, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:27.2":{"pli":"Tuvaṭakaattadaṇḍasāriputtā; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:27.3":{"pli":"Soḷasasuttadharo catutthamhi, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:27.4":{"pli":"Aṭṭhakavaggavaroti tamāhu. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:28.1":{"pli":"Magadhe janapade ramaṇīye, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:28.2":{"pli":"Desavare katapuññanivese; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:28.3":{"pli":"Pāsāṇakacetiyavare suvibhatte, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:28.4":{"pli":"Vasi bhagavā gaṇaseṭṭho. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:29.1":{"pli":"Ubhayavāsamāgatiyamhi, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:29.2":{"pli":"Dvādasayojaniyā parisāya; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:29.3":{"pli":"Soḷasabrāhmaṇānaṃ kira puṭṭho, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:29.4":{"pli":"Pucchāya soḷasapañhakammiyā; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:29.5":{"pli":"Nippakāsayi dhammamadāsi. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:30.1":{"pli":"Atthapakāsakabyañjanapuṇṇaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:30.2":{"pli":"Dhammamadesesi parakhemajaniyaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:30.3":{"pli":"Lokahitāya jino dvipadaggo, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:30.4":{"pli":"Suttavaraṃ bahudhammavicitraṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:30.5":{"pli":"Sabbakilesapamocanahetuṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:30.6":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:31.1":{"pli":"Byañjanamatthapadaṃ samayuttaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:31.2":{"pli":"Akkharasaññitaopamagāḷhaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:31.3":{"pli":"Lokavicāraṇañāṇapabhaggaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:31.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:32.1":{"pli":"Rāgamale amalaṃ vimalaggaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:32.2":{"pli":"Dosamale amalaṃ vimalaggaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:32.3":{"pli":"Mohamale amalaṃ vimalaggaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:32.4":{"pli":"Lokavicāraṇañāṇapabhaggaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:32.5":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:33.1":{"pli":"Klesamale amalaṃ vimalaggaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:33.2":{"pli":"Duccaritamale amalaṃ vimalaggaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:33.3":{"pli":"Lokavicāraṇañāṇapabhaggaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:33.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:34.1":{"pli":"Āsavabandhanayogākilesaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:34.2":{"pli":"Nīvaraṇāni ca tīṇi malāni; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:34.3":{"pli":"Tassa kilesapamocanahetuṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:34.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:35.1":{"pli":"Nimmalasabbakilesapanūdaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:35.2":{"pli":"Rāgavirāgamanejamasokaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:35.3":{"pli":"Santapaṇītasududdasadhammaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:35.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:36.1":{"pli":"Rāgañca dosakamabhañjitasantaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:36.2":{"pli":"Yonicatuggatipañcaviññāṇaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:36.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāratacchadanatāṇalatāpamokkhaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:36.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:37.1":{"pli":"Gambhīraduddasasaṇhanipuṇaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:37.2":{"pli":"Paṇḍitavedaniyaṃ nipuṇatthaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:37.3":{"pli":"Lokavicāraṇañāṇapabhaggaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:37.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:38.1":{"pli":"Navaṅgakusumamālagīveyyaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:38.2":{"pli":"Indriyajhānavimokkhavibhattaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:38.3":{"pli":"Aṭṭhaṅgamaggadharaṃ varayānaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:38.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:39.1":{"pli":"Somupamaṃ vimalaṃ parisuddhaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:39.2":{"pli":"Aṇṇavamūpamaratanasucittaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:39.3":{"pli":"Pupphasamaṃ ravimūpamatejaṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:39.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggo. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.19:40.1":{"pli":"Khemasivaṃ sukhasītalasantaṃ, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:40.2":{"pli":"Maccutatāṇaparaṃ paramatthaṃ; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:40.3":{"pli":"Tassa sunibbutadassanahetuṃ, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.19:40.4":{"pli":"Desayi suttavaraṃ dvipadaggoti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.19:40.5":{"pli":"Suttanipātapāḷi samattā. ","eng":"The Anthology of Discourses is completed. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.2":{"snp5.2:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.2 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.2 ","html":"<article id='snp5.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.2:0.2":{"pli":"Ajitamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Ajita ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.2:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassu nivuto loko, ","eng":"“By what is the world shrouded?” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā ajito) ","eng":"said Venerable Ajita. ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:1.3":{"pli":"Kenassu nappakāsati; ","eng":"“Why does it not shine? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:1.4":{"pli":"Kissābhilepanaṃ brūsi, ","eng":"Tell me, what is its tar pit? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:1.5":{"pli":"Kiṃsu tassa mahabbhayaṃ”. ","eng":"What is its greatest fear?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:2.1":{"pli":"“Avijjāya nivuto loko, ","eng":"“The world is shrouded in ignorance.” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:2.2":{"pli":"(ajitāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha. ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:2.3":{"pli":"Vevicchā pamādā nappakāsati; ","eng":"“Avarice and negligence make it not shine. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:2.4":{"pli":"Jappābhilepanaṃ brūmi, ","eng":"Muttered prayer is its tar pit. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:2.5":{"pli":"Dukkhamassa mahabbhayaṃ”. ","eng":"Suffering is its greatest fear.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:3.1":{"pli":"“Savanti sabbadhi sotā, ","eng":"“The streams flow everywhere,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The same verse was asked of Mahāvīra at Isibhāsiyāiṁ 29.1. The answers are quite different, however, as the Buddha directly addresses the question whereas Mahāvīra’s response is more oblique. "},"snp5.2:3.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā ajito) ","eng":"said Venerable Ajita. ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:3.3":{"pli":"Sotānaṃ kiṃ nivāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"“What is there to block them? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:3.4":{"pli":"Sotānaṃ saṃvaraṃ brūhi, ","eng":"And tell me the restraint of streams—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:3.5":{"pli":"Kena sotā pidhiyyare”. ","eng":"by what are they locked out?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:4.1":{"pli":"“Yāni sotāni lokasmiṃ, ","eng":"“The streams in the world,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:4.2":{"pli":"(ajitāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:4.3":{"pli":"Sati tesaṃ nivāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"“are blocked by mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:4.4":{"pli":"Sotānaṃ saṃvaraṃ brūmi, ","eng":"I tell you the restraint of streams—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:4.5":{"pli":"Paññāyete pidhiyyare”. ","eng":"they are locked out by wisdom.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:5.1":{"pli":"“Paññā ceva sati yañca, ","eng":"“That wisdom and mindfulness,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:5.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā ajito) ","eng":"said Venerable Ajita, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:5.3":{"pli":"Nāmarūpañca mārisa; ","eng":"“and that which is name and form, good fellow; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:5.4":{"pli":"Etaṃ me puṭṭho pabrūhi, ","eng":"when questioned, please tell me of this: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:5.5":{"pli":"Katthetaṃ uparujjhati”. ","eng":"where does this all cease?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:6.1":{"pli":"“Yametaṃ pañhaṃ apucchi, ","eng":"“This question which you have asked, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:6.2":{"pli":"ajita taṃ vadāmi te; ","eng":"I shall answer you, Ajita. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:6.3":{"pli":"Yattha nāmañca rūpañca, ","eng":"Where name and form ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:6.4":{"pli":"asesaṃ uparujjhati; ","eng":"cease with nothing left over—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:6.5":{"pli":"Viññāṇassa nirodhena, ","eng":"with the cessation of consciousness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:6.6":{"pli":"etthetaṃ uparujjhati”. ","eng":"here they cease.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:7.1":{"pli":"“Ye ca saṅkhātadhammāse, ","eng":"“There are those who have appraised the teaching, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"“Appraised” is <i lang='pi' translate='no'>saṅkhāta</i>, literally “calculated, enumerated”. | <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Dhammāse</i> is an archaic masculine nominative plural found only in poetry (eg. <i lang='pi' translate='no'>sāvakāse</i> at <a href='index.html?q=dn21#1.12.11'>DN 21:1.12.11</a>, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>gatāse</i> at <a href='index.html?q=sn1.37#9.1'>SN 1.37:9.1</a>). "},"snp5.2:7.2":{"pli":"ye ca sekhā puthū idha; ","eng":"and many kinds of trainees here. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:7.3":{"pli":"Tesaṃ me nipako iriyaṃ, ","eng":"Now you, being alert, are asked ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:7.4":{"pli":"puṭṭho pabrūhi mārisa”. ","eng":"to tell me their behavior, good fellow.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.2:8.1":{"pli":"“Kāmesu nābhigijjheyya, ","eng":"“Not greedy for sensual pleasures, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:8.2":{"pli":"Manasānāvilo siyā; ","eng":"their mind would be unclouded. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:8.3":{"pli":"Kusalo sabbadhammānaṃ, ","eng":"Skilled in all things, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.2:8.4":{"pli":"Sato bhikkhu paribbaje”ti. ","eng":"a mendicant would wander mindful.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.2:8.5":{"pli":"Ajitamāṇavapucchā paṭhamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.3":{"snp5.3:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.3 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.3 ","html":"<article id='snp5.3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.3:0.2":{"pli":"Tissametteyyamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Tissametteyya ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.3:1.1":{"pli":"“Kodha santusito loke, ","eng":"“Who here in the world is content?” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā tissametteyyo) ","eng":"said Venerable Tissametteyya. ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:1.3":{"pli":"Kassa no santi iñjitā; ","eng":"“Who has no disturbances? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:1.4":{"pli":"Ko ubhantamabhiññāya, ","eng":"What thoughtful one, having known both ends, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"I take <i lang='pi' translate='no'>mantā</i> as an agent noun in nominative, by analogy with similar phrases such as <a href='index.html?q=snp2.2#12.4'>Snp 2.2:12.4</a>, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>na lippati diṭṭhasutesu dhīro</i>. "},"snp5.3:1.5":{"pli":"Majjhe mantā na lippati; ","eng":"is not stuck in the middle? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:1.6":{"pli":"Kaṃ brūsi mahāpurisoti, ","eng":"Who do they say is a great man? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:1.7":{"pli":"Ko idha sibbinimaccagā”. ","eng":"Who here has escaped the seamstress?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.3:2.1":{"pli":"“Kāmesu brahmacariyavā, ","eng":"“Leading the spiritual life among sensual pleasures,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:2.2":{"pli":"(metteyyāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:2.3":{"pli":"Vītataṇho sadā sato; ","eng":"“rid of craving, ever mindful; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:2.4":{"pli":"Saṅkhāya nibbuto bhikkhu, ","eng":"a mendicant who, after appraisal, is quenched: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:2.5":{"pli":"Tassa no santi iñjitā. ","eng":"that’s who has no disturbances. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.3:3.1":{"pli":"So ubhantamabhiññāya, ","eng":"That thoughtful one, having known both ends, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:3.2":{"pli":"Majjhe mantā na lippati; ","eng":"is not stuck in the middle. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:3.3":{"pli":"Taṃ brūmi mahāpurisoti, ","eng":"He is a great man, I declare, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.3:3.4":{"pli":"So idha sibbinimaccagā”ti. ","eng":"he has escaped the seamstress here.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.3:3.5":{"pli":"Tissametteyyamāṇavapucchā dutiyā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.4":{"snp5.4:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.4 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.4 ","html":"<article id='snp5.4'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.4:0.2":{"pli":"Puṇṇakamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Puṇṇaka ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.4:1.1":{"pli":"“Anejaṃ mūladassāviṃ, ","eng":"“To the imperturbable, the seer of the root,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā puṇṇako) ","eng":"said Venerable Puṇṇaka, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:1.3":{"pli":"Atthi pañhena āgamaṃ; ","eng":"“I have come seeking with a question. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:1.4":{"pli":"Kiṃ nissitā isayo manujā, ","eng":"On what grounds have seers and men, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:1.5":{"pli":"Khattiyā brāhmaṇā devatānaṃ; ","eng":"aristocrats and brahmins here in the world ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:1.6":{"pli":"Yaññamakappayiṃsu puthūdha loke, ","eng":"performed so many different <j>sacrifices to the gods? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:1.7":{"pli":"Pucchāmi taṃ bhagavā brūhi me taṃ”. ","eng":"I ask you, Blessed One; please tell me this.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.4:2.1":{"pli":"“Ye kecime isayo manujā, ","eng":"“Whatever seers and men,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:2.2":{"pli":"(puṇṇakāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:2.3":{"pli":"Khattiyā brāhmaṇā devatānaṃ; ","eng":"“aristocrats and brahmins here in the world ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:2.4":{"pli":"Yaññamakappayiṃsu puthūdha loke, ","eng":"have performed so many different <j>sacrifices to the gods: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:2.5":{"pli":"Āsīsamānā puṇṇaka itthattaṃ; ","eng":"all performed sacrifices bound to old age, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:2.6":{"pli":"Jaraṃ sitā yaññamakappayiṃsu”. ","eng":"longing for this place.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.4:3.1":{"pli":"“Ye kecime isayo manujā, ","eng":"“As to those seers and men,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:3.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā puṇṇako) ","eng":"said Venerable Puṇṇaka, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:3.3":{"pli":"Khattiyā brāhmaṇā devatānaṃ; ","eng":"“and aristocrats and brahmins here in the world ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:3.4":{"pli":"Yaññamakappayiṃsu puthūdha loke, ","eng":"who have performed so many different <j>sacrifices to the gods: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:3.5":{"pli":"Kaccissu te bhagavā yaññapathe appamattā; ","eng":"being diligent in the technique of sacrifice, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:3.6":{"pli":"Atāruṃ jātiñca jarañca mārisa, ","eng":"have they crossed over rebirth and old age, good fellow? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:3.7":{"pli":"Pucchāmi taṃ bhagavā brūhi me taṃ”. ","eng":"I ask you, Blessed One; please tell me this.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.4:4.1":{"pli":"“Āsīsanti thomayanti abhijappanti juhanti, ","eng":"“Hoping, invoking, praying, and worshiping,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:4.2":{"pli":"(puṇṇakāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:4.3":{"pli":"Kāmābhijappanti paṭicca lābhaṃ; ","eng":"“they pray for pleasure derived from profit. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:4.4":{"pli":"Te yājayogā bhavarāgarattā, ","eng":"Devoted to sacrifice, besotted by rebirth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:4.5":{"pli":"Nātariṃsu jātijaranti brūmi”. ","eng":"they’ve not crossed over rebirth and old age, <j>I declare.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.4:5.1":{"pli":"“Te ce nātariṃsu yājayogā, ","eng":"“If those devoted to sacrifice,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:5.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā puṇṇako) ","eng":"said Venerable Puṇṇaka, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:5.3":{"pli":"Yaññehi jātiñca jarañca mārisa; ","eng":"“have not, by sacrificing, <j>crossed over rebirth and old age, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:5.4":{"pli":"Atha ko carahi devamanussaloke, ","eng":"who then in the world of gods and humans ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:5.5":{"pli":"Atāri jātiñca jarañca mārisa; ","eng":"has crossed over rebirth and old age, good fellow? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:5.6":{"pli":"Pucchāmi taṃ bhagavā brūhi me taṃ”. ","eng":"I ask you, Blessed One; please tell me this.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.4:6.1":{"pli":"“Saṅkhāya lokasmi paroparāni, ","eng":"“Having appraised the world high and low,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:6.2":{"pli":"(puṇṇakāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:6.3":{"pli":"Yassiñjitaṃ natthi kuhiñci loke; ","eng":"“there is nothing in the world that disturbs them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:6.4":{"pli":"Santo vidhūmo anīgho nirāso, ","eng":"Peaceful, unclouded, untroubled, <j>with no need for hope—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.4:6.5":{"pli":"Atāri so jātijaranti brūmī”ti. ","eng":"they’ve crossed over rebirth and old age, I declare.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.4:6.6":{"pli":"Puṇṇakamāṇavapucchā tatiyā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.5":{"snp5.5:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.5 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.5 ","html":"<article id='snp5.5'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.5:0.2":{"pli":"Mettagūmāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Mettagū ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.5:1.1":{"pli":"“Pucchāmi taṃ bhagavā brūhi me taṃ, ","eng":"“I ask you, Blessed One; please tell me this,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā mettagū) ","eng":"said Venerable Mettagū, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:1.3":{"pli":"Maññāmi taṃ vedaguṃ bhāvitattaṃ; ","eng":"“for I think you are a knowledge master, evolved. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:1.4":{"pli":"Kuto nu dukkhā samudāgatā ime, ","eng":"Where do all these sufferings come from, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:1.5":{"pli":"Ye keci lokasmimanekarūpā”. ","eng":"in all their countless forms in the world?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:2.1":{"pli":"“Dukkhassa ve maṃ pabhavaṃ apucchasi, ","eng":"“You have rightly asked me of the origin of suffering,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:2.2":{"pli":"(mettagūti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:2.3":{"pli":"Taṃ te pavakkhāmi yathā pajānaṃ; ","eng":"“I shall tell you as I understand it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:2.4":{"pli":"Upadhinidānā pabhavanti dukkhā, ","eng":"Attachment is the source of suffering ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:2.5":{"pli":"Ye keci lokasmimanekarūpā. ","eng":"in all its countless forms in the world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:3.1":{"pli":"Yo ve avidvā upadhiṃ karoti, ","eng":"When an ignorant person builds up attachments, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:3.2":{"pli":"Punappunaṃ dukkhamupeti mando; ","eng":"that dullard returns to suffering again and again. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:3.3":{"pli":"Tasmā pajānaṃ upadhiṃ na kayirā, ","eng":"So let one who understands <j>not build up attachments, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:3.4":{"pli":"Dukkhassa jātippabhavānupassī”. ","eng":"contemplating the inception of suffering and rebirth.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"Niddesa treats <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jāti</i> only as “rebirth” and does not connect it with <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pabhava</i> in the sense of “origin”. Commentary glosses with <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jātikāraṇa</i>, which at <a href='index.html?q=sn3.24#4.4'>SN 3.24:4.4</a> glosses <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jātipaccaya</i> , where it must mean “by reason of birth”. "},"snp5.5:4.1":{"pli":"“Yaṃ taṃ apucchimha akittayī no, ","eng":"“Whatever I asked you have explained to me. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:4.2":{"pli":"Aññaṃ taṃ pucchāma tadiṅgha brūhi; ","eng":"I ask you once more, please tell me this: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:4.3":{"pli":"Kathaṃ nu dhīrā vitaranti oghaṃ, ","eng":"How do the attentive cross the flood ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:4.4":{"pli":"Jātiṃ jaraṃ sokapariddavañca; ","eng":"of rebirth, old age, sorrow, and lamenting? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:4.5":{"pli":"Taṃ me muni sādhu viyākarohi, ","eng":"Please, sage, answer me clearly, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:4.6":{"pli":"Tathā hi te vidito esa dhammo”. ","eng":"for truly you understand this matter.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:5.1":{"pli":"“Kittayissāmi te dhammaṃ, ","eng":"“I shall extol a teaching to you,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:5.2":{"pli":"(mettagūti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:5.3":{"pli":"Diṭṭhe dhamme anītihaṃ; ","eng":"“that is apparent in the present, <j>not relying on tradition. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:5.4":{"pli":"Yaṃ viditvā sato caraṃ, ","eng":"Having understood it, one who lives mindfully ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:5.5":{"pli":"Tare loke visattikaṃ”. ","eng":"may cross over clinging in the world.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:6.1":{"pli":"“Tañcāhaṃ abhinandāmi, ","eng":"“And I rejoice, great seer, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:6.2":{"pli":"mahesi dhammamuttamaṃ; ","eng":"in that supreme teaching, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:6.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ viditvā sato caraṃ, ","eng":"having understood which, one who lives mindfully ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:6.4":{"pli":"tare loke visattikaṃ”. ","eng":"may cross over clinging in the world.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:7.1":{"pli":"“Yaṃ kiñci sampajānāsi, ","eng":"“Once you’ve expelled relishing and dogmatism,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:7.2":{"pli":"(mettagūti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:7.3":{"pli":"Uddhaṃ adho tiriyañcāpi majjhe; ","eng":"“regarding everything you are aware of—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:7.4":{"pli":"Etesu nandiñca nivesanañca, ","eng":"above, below, all round, between—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Taking <i lang='pi' translate='no'>nivesana</i> here as “dogma”, the same sense as in the Aṭṭhakavagga. Otherwise it might just mean “strong attachment”. "},"snp5.5:7.5":{"pli":"Panujja viññāṇaṃ bhave na tiṭṭhe. ","eng":"having cast aside consciousness, don’t continue in existence. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:8.1":{"pli":"Evaṃvihārī sato appamatto, ","eng":"A mendicant who wanders meditating like this, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:8.2":{"pli":"Bhikkhu caraṃ hitvā mamāyitāni; ","eng":"diligent and mindful, calling nothing their own, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:8.3":{"pli":"Jātiṃ jaraṃ sokapariddavañca, ","eng":"would, being wise, give up the suffering ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:8.4":{"pli":"Idheva vidvā pajaheyya dukkhaṃ”. ","eng":"of rebirth, old age, sorrow and lamenting right here.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:9.1":{"pli":"“Etābhinandāmi vaco mahesino, ","eng":"“I rejoice in the words of the great seer! ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:9.2":{"pli":"Sukittitaṃ gotamanūpadhīkaṃ; ","eng":"You have expounded non-attachment well, Gotama. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:9.3":{"pli":"Addhā hi bhagavā pahāsi dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Clearly the Buddha has given up suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:9.4":{"pli":"Tathā hi te vidito esa dhammo. ","eng":"for truly you understand this matter. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:10.1":{"pli":"Te cāpi nūnappajaheyyu dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Surely those you’d regularly instruct ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:10.2":{"pli":"Ye tvaṃ muni aṭṭhitaṃ ovadeyya; ","eng":"would also give up suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:10.3":{"pli":"Taṃ taṃ namassāmi samecca nāga, ","eng":"Having met, I bow especially to you, <j>O spiritual giant; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The expression <i lang='pi' translate='no'>taṁ taṁ namassāmi</i> also occurs at <a href='index.html?q=snp5.6#3.3'>Snp 5.6:3.3</a> and <a href='index.html?q=ja159#1.3'>Ja 159:1.3</a>. In each case the context is similar: it is an address in second person, followed by a wish or aspiration. The commentary explains the phrase either as <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tasmā taṁ</i> (“therefore I bow to you”) or as <i lang='pi' translate='no'>taṁ evarūpaṁ</i> (“I bow to you of such a kind”). The Niddesa ignores the doubled pronoun, which implies it did not give it any special significance (<a href='index.html?q=cnd8#93.1'>Cnd 8:93.1</a>). I take it as emphatic: “I bow especially to you”. "},"snp5.5:10.4":{"pli":"Appeva maṃ bhagavā aṭṭhitaṃ ovadeyya”. ","eng":"hopefully the Buddha may regularly instruct me.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:11.1":{"pli":"“Yaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ vedagumābhijaññā, ","eng":"“Any brahmin recognized as a knowledge master, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:11.2":{"pli":"Akiñcanaṃ kāmabhave asattaṃ; ","eng":"who has nothing, unattached to sensual life, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:11.3":{"pli":"Addhā hi so oghamimaṃ atāri, ","eng":"clearly has crossed this flood, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:11.4":{"pli":"Tiṇṇo ca pāraṃ akhilo akaṅkho. ","eng":"crossed to the far shore, kind, wishless. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.5:12.1":{"pli":"Vidvā ca yo vedagū naro idha, ","eng":"And a wise person here, a knowledge master, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:12.2":{"pli":"Bhavābhave saṅgamimaṃ visajja; ","eng":"having untied the bond to life after life, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:12.3":{"pli":"So vītataṇho anīgho nirāso, ","eng":"free of craving, untroubled, with no need for hope, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.5:12.4":{"pli":"Atāri so jātijaranti brūmī”ti. ","eng":"has crossed over rebirth and old age, I declare.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.5:12.5":{"pli":"Mettagūmāṇavapucchā catutthī. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}